{
  "texts": [
    "The authors used Classical Arabic NER corpus (CANER Corpus) which is annotated NER corpus manually and it contains approx.",
    "258,264 words and 72,108 named entities.",
    "According to the evaluation of the proposed approach, it achieved an F1-measure of 89.5%, a recall rate of 89.3%, and an accuracy rate of 90.2%.",
    "Sasidhar et al. [65] discussed rule-based techniques for Telugu language and the recognition of Named Entities using a variety of characteristics, gazetteer lists employing languagedependent features and other features.",
    "In this section the authors covered the two parts of named entity recognition."
  ]
}